==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: forthcoming
<hw>forth"com`ing</hw> <pr>(f⟦omac⟧rth"k⟦ucr⟧m`⟦icr⟧ng <it>or</it>
f⟦omac⟧rth`k⟦ucr⟧m"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Ready
or about to appear; making appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Candid; frank; not withholding relevant information;
cooperative in providing information.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having an agreeable and sociable personality;
friendly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Available or ready at the time required; <as>as,
payment will be <ex>forthcoming</ex> on receipt of the
goods</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forthgoing</ent>⟦br⟧
